\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0025:question:Eng}]
	The Fibonacci sequence is defined by the recurrence relation:
	\medskip%
	\begin{center}
		\( {F}_{n} \equal {F}_{ n \minus 1 } \mathplus {F}_{ n \minus 2 } \),
		where \( {F}_{1} \equal 1 \) and \( {F}_{2} \equal 1 \).
	\end{center}
	\medskip%
	Hence the first 12 terms will be:
	\begin{align*}
		{F}_{1} &\equal  1 & {F}_{2} &\equal  1 & {F}_{3} &\equal  2 & {F}_{4}  &\equal  3 & {F}_{5}  &\equal  5 & {F}_{6}  &\equal 8 \\%
		{F}_{7} &\equal 13 & {F}_{8} &\equal 21 & {F}_{9} &\equal 34 & {F}_{10} &\equal 55 & {F}_{11} &\equal 89 & {F}_{12} &\equal 144 %
	\end{align*}
	The 12th term, \( {F}_{12} \), is the first term to contain three digits.

	What is the index of the first term in the Fibonacci sequence to contain 1000 digits?
	\par\hrefOriginalPage{25}%
\tcbline%
	フィボナッチ数列は以下の漸化式で定義される：
	\medskip%
	\begin{center}
		\( {F}_{n} \equal {F}_{ n \minus 1 } \mathplus {F}_{ n \minus 2 } \)，
		ただし\( {F}_{1} \equal 1 \) and \( {F}_{2} \equal 1 \)．
	\end{center}
	\medskip%
	最初の12項は以下である．
	\begin{align*}
		{F}_{1} &\equal  1 & {F}_{2} &\equal  1 & {F}_{3} &\equal  2 & {F}_{4}  &\equal  3 & {F}_{5}  &\equal  5 & {F}_{6}  &\equal 8 \\%
		{F}_{7} &\equal 13 & {F}_{8} &\equal 21 & {F}_{9} &\equal 34 & {F}_{10} &\equal 55 & {F}_{11} &\equal 89 & {F}_{12} &\equal 144 %
	\end{align*}
	12番目の項，\( {F}_{12} \)が3桁になる最初の項である．\par%
	1000桁になる最初の項の番号を答えよ．
	\par\hrefTransitionPageJpn{25}%
\end{tcbProblem}
